I have mild Von Willebrand disease. It is a condition that can cause extended or excessive bleeding. The cause of von Willebrand disease is a deficiency in or impairment of a protein called von Willebrand factor, an important component in your blood-clotting process. In general, it takes longer for people with von Willebrand disease to form clots and stop bleeding when they're cut.

In case of any major surgery, I will need DDVAP.
None, only DDVAP in case of major surgery.
